or merchandise directly to the consumer, including food or beverages for
off-premises consumption, household products, personal grooming and health
products, and other consumer goods, with the majority of items being offered for sale
at lower than the typical market price.
(b) Small box discount retail does not include any of the following:
(i) Businesses that dedicate at least fifteen percent of floor area to fresh
foods and vegetables.
(ii) Businesses that contain a prescription pharmacy.
(iii) Businesses that sell gasoline or diesel fuel.
(iv) Businesses that contain a majority of goods that serve the purpose of
home improvement or construction.
§273. Workplace safety plan; requirement to sumbit
A.(1) Every small box discount retail employer shall develop and implement,
or provide a timeline no longer than six months to implement, a written workforce
safety plan.
(2) If a small box discount retailer employer already has a written workforce
safety plan in place, that plan shall satisfy the requirements of Paragraph (1) of this
Subsection.
B. Every small box discount retail employer shall submit its written
workforce safety plan to the secretary of Louisiana Works.
Section 2. The secretary of Louisiana Works shall promulgate and adopt rules to
provide for the submission of workplace safety plans as required by the provisions of R.S.
23:273 as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.
